Run the Initialization Command: npm init -y
This will create a package.json file in your project folder. This file will store information about your project, including dependencies (libraries you'll use). The -y flag automatically agrees to the default settings.
Install http-server:
npm install -g http-server
Start the Server:
http-server

Testing on Your iPhone

Keep the Server Running:

Make sure http-server is still running: Double-check that the terminal window with your http-server is still open and that the server is active.

Open in Edge on Your iPhone:

Connect to the Same Wi-Fi: Make sure both your Mac and your iPhone are connected to the same Wi-Fi network.
Open Safari: Open the Safari app on your iPhone.
Enter the URL: In the address bar of Safari, type the same URL that you used in your browser on your Mac (e.g., http://localhost:8080).


Choose a Hosting Provider:

Free Hosting: There are many free hosting providers that can host your PWA. Some popular options include:
Netlify (https://www.netlify.com/)
Vercel (https://vercel.com/)
GitHub Pages (https://pages.github.com/)

Paid Hosting: If you need more control or features, you can choose a paid hosting provider like:
Amazon S3 (https://aws.amazon.com/s3/)
Google Cloud Storage (https://cloud.google.com/storage/)
DigitalOcean Spaces (https://www.digitalocean.com/products/spaces/)



